"title": "4418: bread",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4418",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The basic component of the staple diet in biblical times. Consecrated bread was continually laid out in the Holy Place of the tabernacle and temple. Jesus Christ called himself the bread of life.</p>\n<h2>Bread the basic component of the diet</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:11\">MAT 6:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:3\">LUK 11:3</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:18\">GEN 14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:3-Gen18:6\">GEN 18:3–18:6</a> <em>Abraham entertains the three angels</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:34\">GEN 25:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:17\">GEN 27:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:23\">GEN 45:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:7-Deut8:9\">DEU 8:7–8:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:4\">DEU 23:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:5-Judg8:6\">JDG 8:5–8:6</a> <em>Gideon asks for bread for his troops</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:19\">JDG 19:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:14\">RUT 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:36\">1SA 2:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:17\">1SA 17:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:2-1Sam21:3\">1SA 21:2–21:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:7-1Sam25:11\">1SA 25:7–25:11</a> <em>Nabal refuses bread to David's men</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:7-1Kgs13:22\">1KI 13:7–13:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:10-1Kgs17:16\">1KI 17:10–17:16</a> <em>The widow at Zarephath feeds Elijah and is rewarded</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:5-1Kgs19:6\">1KI 19:5–19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job23:12\">JOB 23:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:14-Ps104:15\">PSA 104:14–104:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:8\">PRO 30:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:16\">ISA 33:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:14\">ISA 51:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:2\">ISA 55:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer37:21\">JER 37:21</a> <em>Jeremiah's rations in prison</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer42:14\">JER 42:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:6\">LAM 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:9\">EZK 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:3\">DEU 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:3-Matt4:4\">MAT 4:3–4:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:3-Luke4:4\">LUK 4:3–4:4</a> <em>the temptation of Jesus Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:8\">MRK 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:10\">2CO 9:10</a></p>\n<h2>A diet consisting solely of bread was indicative of deprivation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:27\">1KI 22:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:26\">2CH 18:26</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:26\">PRO 6:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:11\">LAM 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:12\">LAM 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:4\">LAM 4:4</a></p>\n<h2>Kinds of bread</h2>\n<h3>Unleavened bread</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:39\">EXO 12:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:8\">EXO 12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:14-Exod12:20\">EXO 12:14–12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:3-Exod13:7\">EXO 13:3–13:7</a></p>\n<h3>Manna</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:31-Exod16:35\">EXO 16:31–16:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:4-Exod16:8\">EXO 16:4–16:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:11-Exod16:12\">EXO 16:11–16:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:14-Exod16:19\">EXO 16:14–16:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:15\">NEH 9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:23-Ps78:25\">PSA 78:23–78:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:40\">PSA 105:40</a></p>\n<h2>Gifts of bread</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:23\">GEN 45:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:3-1Sam10:4\">1SA 10:3–10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:20\">1SA 16:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:18\">1SA 25:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:19\">2SA 6:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:3\">1CH 16:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:1-2Sam16:2\">2SA 16:1–16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:3\">1KI 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:42\">2KI 4:42</a></p>\n<h2>Offerings of bread</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:11-Lev7:14\">LEV 7:11–7:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:2\">EXO 29:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:32-Exod29:34\">EXO 29:32–29:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:11\">LEV 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:31-Lev8:32\">LEV 8:31–8:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:20\">LEV 23:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:17-Num6:20\">NUM 6:17–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:19-Judg6:21\">JDG 6:19–6:21</a></p>\n<h2>The bread of the Presence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:5-Lev24:8\">LEV 24:5–24:8</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:23-Exod25:30\">EXO 25:23–25:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:10-Exod35:13\">EXO 35:10–35:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:33-Exod39:36\">EXO 39:33–39:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:22-Exod40:23\">EXO 40:22–40:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:4-Num4:8\">NUM 4:4–4:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:1-1Sam21:6\">1SA 21:1–21:6</a> <em>David and his men eat the consecrated bread</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:31-1Chr9:32\">1CH 9:31–9:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:29\">1CH 23:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:4\">2CH 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:11\">2CH 13:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:32-Neh10:33\">NEH 10:32–10:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:1-Matt12:8\">MAT 12:1–12:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:23-Mark2:28\">MRK 2:23–2:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:1-Luke6:5\">LUK 6:1–6:5</a> <em>Jesus Christ and his disciples in the cornfields on the Sabbath</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:1-Heb9:2\">HEB 9:1–9:2</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the bread of life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:25-John6:35\">JHN 6:25–6:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:41-John6:59\">JHN 6:41–6:59</a></p>\n<h2>Miracles of multiplication of bread</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:13-Matt14:21\">MAT 14:13–14:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:32-Mark6:44\">MRK 6:32–6:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:10-Luke9:17\">LUK 9:10–9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:1-John6:13\">JHN 6:1–6:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:32-Matt15:38\">MAT 15:32–15:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:1-Mark8:10\">MRK 8:1–8:10</a></p>\n<h2>The breaking of bread as a symbol of the death of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:29\">MAT 26:26–26:29</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:25\">MRK 14:22–14:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:17-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:17–22:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:24-1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:24–11:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:28-Luke24:35\">LUK 24:28–24:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:46\">ACT 2:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:6-Acts20:7\">ACT 20:6–20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:11\">ACT 20:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:35\">ACT 27:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16-1Cor10:17\">1CO 10:16–10:17</a></p>",
